cs.NI, cs.GT, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.CE 

This paper discusses the economic model of the Internet of Things (IoT) and the strategic interactions among different entities such as IoT service providers, wireless service providers, cloud service providers, and end-users. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category for this paper is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper also involves game theory and optimization techniques to analyze the equilibrium pricing strategy and payoff of providers, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also discusses the impact of advertisement revenue on the equilibrium pricing strategy, which could place it in cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
